&0&6&b June 13, 2016&0

   &0&3&bo&0 Wiki and website upgraded and fixed... (php upgrades took it down)  

   &0&3&bo&0 Immortals can now cast self-only spells on anybody.

   &0&3&bo&0 'show rent' now supports stacking of objects. It also displays
     equipped items correctly.

   &0&3&bo&0 The grant system is working.

   &0&3&bo&0 iedit should be working too.

 &0&6&b November 17 2007 - Rift and Halflife on &3&bNEW&0 &6&bhardware!!&0

   &0&3&bo&0 Please check things to make sure you have all your data and 
     things function as expected.

   &0&3&bo&0 So far the only potential issue I've noticed is that the NFS
     mount of the development directories between the boxes didn't
     seem to behave in an automated fashion.  They are up now but
     I'm not sure how well they'd recover in a reboot.

   &0&3&bo&0 Additionally, rift will not reboot, if it goes down currently
     I'll need to drive in and press the power button. Halflife
     will spottily reboot cleanly, sometimes I need to hit f1 to
     continue to boot, sometimes I don't, almond joy has nuts,
     rift don't.

   &0&3&bo&0 I think all the packages necessary to develop are installed
     on halflife, and all files necessary for our existance are
     in place.

   &0&3&bo&0 Check out the new look to Doxygen on rift.  Since you guys
     had to have it :P  I'm not sure if it offers any additional
     functionality but I'm sure as coders you will be able to tell.

   &0&3&bo&0 Be sure to add yourself to the iptables on rift.  Once you
     do you can jump from rift to halflife build yourself a dev
     mud there then boot it up to add yourself to the iptables
     on hafllife so you no longer have to jump through rift.

   &0&3&bo&0 Generally, I'd like to know sooner than later if we're
     going to develop issues.  I know I've completely lost my
     mind, but I'm going to look at bios and microcode upgrades
     for the boxes in the coming months.  If they fry I'm going
     to just cry.

   &0&3&bo&0 Insure++ is gone for good now I think.  I hope there
     are other memory checking tools we can make use of.

   &0&3&bo&0 As mentioned in another post the ssh keys are now different
     for rift so the cross site backups probably need close
     inspection and perhaps rework.

 -- Zzur&0

